<DocsLayout title="BACKLOG: GreenScape" description="8 tickets from empty directory to live site.">
  <h1 class="mb-4">Backlog: GreenScape Landscaping</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">8 tickets from empty directory to live site. You'll paste this into your project as <code class="bg-bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">BACKLOG.md</code>.</p>

  <details class="mb-8 border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <summary>Copy full backlog as markdown</summary>
    <div class="p-4">
      <CodeBlock copy>{`# BACKLOG

## Ticket 1: Project Setup
**Labels:** setup | **Size:** S | **Dependencies:** None

Create the GitHub repository, copy CLAUDE.md and BACKLOG.md into it, set up the initial project structure. Create GitHub labels (setup, frontend, deploy), create Issues for all tickets, and create a GitHub Project board.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] GitHub repository exists with CLAUDE.md and BACKLOG.md committed
- [ ] GitHub labels created: setup, frontend, deploy
- [ ] GitHub Issues created for all tickets in this backlog
- [ ] GitHub Project board created with columns: To Do, In Progress, Done
- [ ] All Issues added to the Project board in the To Do column
- [ ] .gitignore includes node_modules, dist, .env

---

## Ticket 2: Development Environment
**Labels:** setup | **Size:** S | **Dependencies:** Ticket 1

Initialise the React + Vite project with Tailwind CSS. Create the basic file structure from CLAUDE.md. Create the Makefile. Create the content data file with placeholder text.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] make dev starts the Vite development server on localhost:5173
- [ ] Browser shows "GreenScape Landscaping" as the page title
- [ ] Tailwind CSS is working (utility class renders correctly)
- [ ] make lint runs ESLint without errors
- [ ] src/data/content.js exists with placeholder content for all sections
- [ ] Repository structure matches CLAUDE.md

---

## Ticket 3: Site Layout & Navigation
**Labels:** frontend | **Size:** M | **Dependencies:** Ticket 2

Sticky header with logo and navigation links, main content area, footer. Navigation links scroll to sections. Responsive with mobile hamburger menu.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Header displays business name and navigation links
- [ ] Clicking a nav link smooth-scrolls to the section
- [ ] Header remains visible when scrolling (sticky)
- [ ] Footer displays copyright year and contact info
- [ ] Mobile: navigation collapses into hamburger menu
- [ ] Desktop: navigation links displayed horizontally
- [ ] Colours and fonts match the design tokens in CLAUDE.md

---

## Ticket 4: Hero & Services Section
**Labels:** frontend | **Size:** M | **Dependencies:** Ticket 3

Hero section with headline, tagline, CTA. Six service cards in a responsive grid. Content from content.js.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Hero displays business name, tagline, and "Get in Touch" CTA
- [ ] CTA button scrolls to the Contact section
- [ ] Hero has background image or colour matching design
- [ ] 6 service cards with icon placeholder, name, and description
- [ ] Grid: 1 column mobile, 2 tablet, 3 desktop
- [ ] All text from content.js, not hardcoded
- [ ] No horizontal scrolling on any screen size

---

## Ticket 5: Testimonials & About Sections
**Labels:** frontend | **Size:** M | **Dependencies:** Ticket 4

Four testimonial cards with star ratings. About section with photo placeholder and bio text.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] 4 testimonials with quote, name, suburb, and 5-star visual
- [ ] Testimonials visually distinct (different background or card style)
- [ ] About section has photo placeholder and 2-3 paragraphs
- [ ] About text max ~700px for readability
- [ ] Star ratings are visual (icons or CSS), not text "5/5"

---

## Ticket 6: Service Area & Contact Sections
**Labels:** frontend | **Size:** M | **Dependencies:** Ticket 5

Suburb list. Contact with clickable phone and email links. No contact form (anti-scope).

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Service area displays all 10 suburbs from the PRD
- [ ] Contact shows phone, email, address, business hours
- [ ] Phone is a tel: link — opens dialer on mobile
- [ ] Email is a mailto: link — opens email client
- [ ] Business hours clearly formatted
- [ ] No contact form exists (anti-scope)

---

## Ticket 7: SEO & Meta Tags
**Labels:** frontend | **Size:** S | **Dependencies:** Ticket 6

Page title, meta description, Open Graph tags, semantic HTML, heading hierarchy.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Page title contains "GreenScape Landscaping" and "Melbourne"
- [ ] Meta description exists (150-160 characters)
- [ ] Open Graph tags: og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url
- [ ] Only one h1 element on the page
- [ ] Heading hierarchy logical: h1 → h2 → h3
- [ ] Semantic HTML: nav, main, section, footer
- [ ] All images have alt text
- [ ] Lighthouse SEO score 90+

---

## Ticket 8: Deploy
**Labels:** deploy | **Size:** S | **Dependencies:** Ticket 7

Deploy to Netlify free tier. Verify the live site matches the development version.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Site deployed to a live URL
- [ ] All sections load correctly on the live site
- [ ] Images load (not broken)
- [ ] Phone tel: link works on a real mobile phone
- [ ] Responsive on the live URL (check on actual phone)
- [ ] Lighthouse performance score 80+
- [ ] Lighthouse SEO score 90+`}</CodeBlock>
    </div>
  </details>

